[1]Design and developmentThe S.22 was a single-seat twin-engine biplane flying boat.
[2]Its two   Isotta Fraschini V.6bis engines were mounted on eight struts above the hull and below the upper wing and drove two propellers, one in a tractor configuration and one in a pusher configuration.Aviation: SIAI racing seaplanes Operational historyDuring test flights over Lake Maggiore prior to the 1921 Schneider trophy races, the S.22 crashed into the lake, ending the hope that it would represent Italy in the races.Aviation: SIAI racing seaplanes
